						<summary>

						<p>On one of the beds in the <hi rend="italic">Pañchapāṇḍavar-paḍukkai</hi> on the hill.</p>						

						<p>This inscription is engraved in Grantha characters of about the 9th10th century and its language is an admixture of Sanskrit and Prākṛit.</p>						

						<p>It records an <hi rend="italic">anāśana-vrata</hi> (fasting) evidently of some jaina monk.</p>						

